reviews.text:
Absolutely beautiful, and gave me and my brother a laugh. 
See photos for it.
trains are frequent here good bus alternatives if there are no trains what would be useful here would be toilets

Experienced a very bad customer service from the ticket officer ‘Joe’. I asked him to renew my weekly pass for 2-5 very clearly but he topped up my Oyster card for £35 and argued as I didn’t advice home to do so.

- 3 self-service Oyster card top up machines, accepts both card and cash
- 2 ticket booths to be helped by staff
- decent sized screen located in convenient locations showing train times/updates
- clean station
- good number of staff
- very spacious in the station, lifts and platforms
- the majority of the TfL trains stop at Chadwell Heath
- bus stop, newsagent, minicab and zebra crossing right outside the station
Useless 3 self service machines only one which except coins and broken for 3 weeks or more  and staff on the phone talking and other one f**** know what he’s do!!!!
